N2  - The article presents a study which explored the impact of the disability of a job applicant on evaluative judgments in the selection process. A brief overview of the research problem and the methodology used in the study is discussed. The subjects of the study and procedures used in the study are detailed. The results of the study are reviewed, and a discussion of it's implications for further research and limitations stemming from the data set used are also examined.
